  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian response to communities affected by the conflict and armed violence in Arauca departmen</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SNPS/Caritas Colombia will respond to the immediate needs of 185 families forcibly displaced from Tame, Savavena and Arauquita due to ongoing combat between different illegal armed actors through the distribution of relief items (WASH, food and NFI). Specifically the response will be structured as follows:
- Implementation will begin with the identification of beneficiaries; an initial identification has been made by using the register of the human rights ombusdspeople in Saravena, Arauquita and Tame as well as information received from parishes. Further families will be identified as the fighting continues and further combat is expected.
- SNPS/Caritas Colombia will then communicate the project objectives; explain the targeting process and share the Feedback and Complaints Handling Mechanism within the targeted communities. 
- Procurement of the relief items will be managed by SNPS/CC in line with standard operating procedures. As far as possible procurement will be made in the capital of Arauca.</narrative>
  </description>
